*libmng-1.0.9-r1 (04 Oct 2006)

  04 Oct 2006; Doug Goldstein <cardoe@gentoo.org> +libmng-1.0.9-r1.ebuild:
  Changing my stance on the jpeg support issue. Reverting back to requiring
  jpeg since it's 'optional' only for Mozilla support according to docs. It
  also changes API and ABI which requires recompiling anything linking to
  this. It does not provide a full MNG build and will not even render many
  types of valid MNG files without this. jpeg is a small library. The benefits
  of keeping this outweight the benefits of removing it.

  04 Oct 2006; Doug Goldstein <cardoe@gentoo.org> libmng-1.0.8-r2.ebuild,
  libmng-1.0.9.ebuild:
  Setting DEPEND and RDEPEND explicitly. Fixed autotools eclass usage.

  04 Oct 2006; Doug Goldstein <cardoe@gentoo.org>
  +files/libmng-1.0.9-jpeg-compile.patch, libmng-1.0.9.ebuild:
  Fix compiling with USE='-jpeg'. without-jpeg didn't really remove the depend.

  14 Apr 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> libmng-1.0.9.ebuild:
  Don't provide zlib useflag as it's an hard-dependency, bug #129928.

